Communicated by:
ProMED

[This week's report has a report on the 1st case of WPV1 associated AFP in Pakistan, multiple cases of cVDPV2 associated AFP involving DR Congo, Nigeria and Somalia, and unfortunately multiple positive environmental samples with cVDPV3 in Israel and the Palestinian Authority.

Unfortunately, both WPV1 and cVDPVs are still occurring. My comment in last week's update (Poliomyelitis update (16): WPV1 AFP Pakistan, cVDPV2, AFP, cVDPV3 ES 20220425.8702827) "Israel seems to have interrupted transmission of cVDPV3" was overly optimistic.

A map showing the locations of each confirmed case of polio worldwide in the past 12 months can be found at https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. One can see cases of cVDPV in a band across Africa and in Israel, Ukraine, Tajikistan, Afghanistan and Pakistan, cVDPV1 in Madagascar and Yemen, and WPV1 in Afghanistan and Pakistan. - Mod.MPP

ProMED map:
Pakistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8702966,140]
